{
  "video_id": "WuyPuH9ojCE",
  "title": "How stress affects your brain - Madhumita Murgia",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6791.0,
      "end_time": 8526.0,
      "text": "Are you sleeping restlessly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 8526.0,
      "end_time": 10299.0,
      "text": "feeling irritable or moody,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 10299.0,
      "end_time": 11839.0,
      "text": "forgetting little things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 11839.0,
      "end_time": 14602.0,
      "text": "and feeling overwhelmed and isolated?"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 14602.0,
      "end_time": 16567.0,
      "text": "Don't worry. We've all been there."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 16567.0,
      "end_time": 18779.0,
      "text": "You're probably just stressed out."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 18779.0,
      "end_time": 20967.0,
      "text": "Stress isn't always a bad thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 20967.0,
      "end_time": 24178.0,
      "text": "It can be handy for a burst of extra energy and focus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 24178.0,
      "end_time": 26589.0,
      "text": "like when you're playing  a competitive sport,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 26589.0,
      "end_time": 28516.0,
      "text": "or have to speak in public."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 28516.0,
      "end_time": 30086.0,
      "text": "But when its continuous,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 30086.0,
      "end_time": 33105.0,
      "text": "the kind most of us face day in and day out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 33105.0,
      "end_time": 36932.0,
      "text": "it actually begins to change your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 36932.0,
      "end_time": 38152.0,
      "text": "Chronic stress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 38152.0,
      "end_time": 41235.0,
      "text": "like being overworked or having arguments at home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 41235.0,
      "end_time": 42778.0,
      "text": "can affect brain size,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 42778.0,
      "end_time": 43966.0,
      "text": "its structure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 43966.0,
      "end_time": 45249.0,
      "text": "and how it functions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 45249.0,
      "end_time": 48249.0,
      "text": "right down to the level of your genes."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 48249.0,
      "end_time": 49980.0,
      "text": "Stress begins with something called"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 49980.0,
      "end_time": 53606.0,
      "text": "the hypothalamus pituitary adrenal axis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 53606.0,
      "end_time": 55698.0,
      "text": "a series of interactions"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 55698.0,
      "end_time": 59579.0,
      "text": "between endocrine glands in the brain and on the kidney,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 59579.0,
      "end_time": 62500.0,
      "text": "which controls your body's reaction to stress."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 62500.0,
      "end_time": 64904.0,
      "text": "When your brain detects a stressful situation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 64904.0,
      "end_time": 68856.0,
      "text": "your HPA axis is instantly activated"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 68856.0,
      "end_time": 75022.0,
      "text": "and releases a hormone called cortisol , which primes your body for instant action."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 75022.0,
      "end_time": 78331.0,
      "text": "But high levels of cortisol over long periods of time"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 78331.0,
      "end_time": 80826.0,
      "text": "wreak havoc on your brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 80826.0,
      "end_time": 84262.0,
      "text": "For example, chronic stress increases the activity level"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 84262.0,
      "end_time": 88277.0,
      "text": "and number of neural connections in the amygdala,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88277.0,
      "end_time": 90489.0,
      "text": "your brain's fear center."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 90489.0,
      "end_time": 92413.0,
      "text": "And as levels of cortisol rise,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 92413.0,
      "end_time": 94760.0,
      "text": "electric signals in your hippocampus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 94760.0,
      "end_time": 99421.0,
      "text": "the part of the brain associated with learning, memories, and stress control"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 99421.0,
      "end_time": 101054.0,
      "text": "deteriorate."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 101054.0,
      "end_time": 105229.0,
      "text": "The hippocampus also inhibits the activity of the HPA axis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 105229.0,
      "end_time": 106511.0,
      "text": "so when it weakens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 106511.0,
      "end_time": 109982.0,
      "text": "so does your ability  to control your stress."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 109982.0,
      "end_time": 111322.0,
      "text": "That's not all, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 111322.0,
      "end_time": 115880.0,
      "text": "Cortisol can literally  cause your brain to shrink in size."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 115880.0,
      "end_time": 120703.0,
      "text": "Too much of it results in the loss of synaptic connections between neurons"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 120703.0,
      "end_time": 123267.0,
      "text": "and the shrinking  of your prefrontal cortex,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 123267.0,
      "end_time": 126871.0,
      "text": "the part of your brain the regulates behaviors like concentration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 126871.0,
      "end_time": 128253.0,
      "text": "decision-making,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 128252.99999999999,
      "end_time": 129378.99999999999,
      "text": "judgement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 129378.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131620.0,
      "text": "and social interaction."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 131620.0,
      "end_time": 136437.0,
      "text": "It also leads to fewer new brain cells being made in the hippocampus."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 136437.0,
      "end_time": 139925.0,
      "text": "This means chronic stress might make it harder for you to learn"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 139925.0,
      "end_time": 141401.0,
      "text": "and remember things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 141401.0,
      "end_time": 144324.0,
      "text": "and also set the stage for more serious mental problems,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 144324.0,
      "end_time": 148875.0,
      "text": "like depression and eventually Alzheimer's disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 148875.0,
      "end_time": 153181.0,
      "text": "The effects of stress may filter right down to your brain's DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 153181.0,
      "end_time": 154497.0,
      "text": "An experiment showed"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 154497.0,
      "end_time": 158706.0,
      "text": "that the amount of nurturing  a mother rat provides its newborn baby"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 158706.0,
      "end_time": 163878.0,
      "text": "plays a part in determining how that baby responds to stress later in life."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 163878.0,
      "end_time": 168336.0,
      "text": "The pups of nurturing moms turned out less sensitive to stress"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 168336.0,
      "end_time": 171769.0,
      "text": "because their brains developed  more cortisol receptors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 171769.0,
      "end_time": 174757.0,
      "text": "which stick to cortisol and dampen the stress response."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 174757.0,
      "end_time": 178223.0,
      "text": "The pups of negligent moms had the opposite outcome,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 178223.0,
      "end_time": 181910.0,
      "text": "and so became more sensitive to stress throughout life."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 181910.0,
      "end_time": 184675.0,
      "text": "These are considered epigenetic changes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 184675.0,
      "end_time": 187524.0,
      "text": "meaning that they affect which genes are expressed"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 187524.0,
      "end_time": 190514.0,
      "text": "without directly changing  the genetic code."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 190514.0,
      "end_time": 194361.0,
      "text": "And these changes can be reversed if the moms are swapped."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 194361.0,
      "end_time": 196123.0,
      "text": "But there's a surprising result."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 196123.0,
      "end_time": 199788.0,
      "text": "The epigenetic changes caused by one single mother rat"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 199788.0,
      "end_time": 203622.0,
      "text": "were passed down to many generations of rats after her."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 203622.0,
      "end_time": 208077.0,
      "text": "In other words, the results  of these actions were inheritable."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 208077.0,
      "end_time": 210417.0,
      "text": "It's not all bad news, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 210417.0,
      "end_time": 214817.0,
      "text": "There are many ways to reverse what cortisol does to your stressed brain."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 214817.0,
      "end_time": 218713.0,
      "text": "The most powerful weapons are exercise and meditation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 218713.0,
      "end_time": 220376.0,
      "text": "which involves breathing deeply"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 220376.0,
      "end_time": 223521.0,
      "text": "and being aware  and focused on your surroundings."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 223521.0,
      "end_time": 226255.0,
      "text": "Both of these activities  decrease your stress"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226255.0,
      "end_time": 229525.0,
      "text": "and increase the size of the hippocampus,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 229525.0,
      "end_time": 231770.0,
      "text": "thereby improving your memory."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 231770.0,
      "end_time": 234470.0,
      "text": "So don't feel defeated  by the pressures of daily life."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 234470.0,
      "end_time": 244470.0,
      "text": "Get in control of your stress before it takes control of you."
    }
  ]
}